Package semantics.ranking

This package provides classes implementing ranking functions for propositional and first-order formulas and conditionals as well as system Z approaches to compute such ranking functions for a knowledge base.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ExplainedRankingFunction<I extends Interpretable>
    Extended version of RankingFunction that returns explanations for each evaluation.
    ExplainedRelationalRankingFunction
    Extended version of RelationalRankingFunction that returns explanations for each evaluation.
    RankingFunction<I extends Interpretable>
    A ranking function provides semantics to qualitative conditionals.
    RelationalRankingFunction
    A relational ranking function extends the idea of a ranking function to the first-order case.
    RelationalSystemZ
    Implementation of a system z-like approach to create a ranking function for a first-order conditional knowledge base.
    SystemZ
    System Z calculates a unique minimal ranking function for a propositional conditional knowledge base.
